  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "A 2-year-old boy is brought to the office by his mother because of a 2-week history of progressive hoarseness. During the past week, he has also had two episodes of cough and shortness of breath that resolved spontaneously. The mother is concerned that these episodes might be “asthmatic crises similar to the ones his grandmother has.” He has no other history of serious illness and takes no medications. His mother did not receive prenatal care but reports an uncomplicated vaginal delivery at 38 weeks' gestation. She was treated for gonorrhea during the first trimester. The patient is not in acute distress. Vital signs are within normal limits. Physical examination shows no abnormalities. Laryngoscopy shows multiple polypoid growths distributed asymmetrically over the true and false vocal folds. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Laryngeal papillomatosis"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Vocal fold nodules"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Reinke edema"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Vocal fold retention cysts"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Chronic laryngitis"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) CORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-section-id=\"rtXfU-\" data-sememe-id=\"Btazfm\">Laryngeal papillomatosis</a> is the most common form of <span class=\"wichtig\"><b><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-section-id=\"rtXfU-\" data-sememe-id=\"Btazfm\">recurrent respiratory papillomatosis</a></b></span> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-section-id=\"rtXfU-\" data-sememe-id=\"Btazfm\">RRP</a>), which develops as a result of <span class=\"wichtig\"><b><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zO0rET&anker=Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-learningcard-id=\"zO0rET\" data-anker=\"Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-section-id=\"CPbqSF\" data-sememe-id=\"4kY3L6\">human papillomavirus</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pn0Wtg&anker=Zcdc83877f75d9d9b9a07ece6544f646c\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pn0Wtg\" data-anker=\"Zcdc83877f75d9d9b9a07ece6544f646c\" data-section-id=\"VacGja0\">virus</a></b></span> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zO0rET&anker=Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-learningcard-id=\"zO0rET\" data-anker=\"Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-section-id=\"CPbqSF\" data-sememe-id=\"4kY3L6\">HPV</a>) <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>infection</b></span> (most commonly <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zO0rET&anker=Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-learningcard-id=\"zO0rET\" data-anker=\"Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-section-id=\"CPbqSF\" data-sememe-id=\"4kY3L6\">HPV</a> 6 and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zO0rET&anker=Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-learningcard-id=\"zO0rET\" data-anker=\"Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-section-id=\"CPbqSF\" data-sememe-id=\"4kY3L6\">HPV</a> 11). <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Juvenile-onset</b></span> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-section-id=\"rtXfU-\" data-sememe-id=\"Btazfm\">RRP</a> usually develops before the age of 5 years and is due to <span class=\"wichtig\"><b><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=d40oRT&anker=Z8916e5f23e9fb026689a4803249d708d\" data-learningcard-id=\"d40oRT\" data-anker=\"Z8916e5f23e9fb026689a4803249d708d\" data-section-id=\"OuXIr-\" data-sememe-id=\"oZX0c9\">vertical transmission</a></b></span> of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zO0rET&anker=Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-learningcard-id=\"zO0rET\" data-anker=\"Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-section-id=\"CPbqSF\" data-sememe-id=\"4kY3L6\">HPV</a> from the mother during vaginal delivery. This patient's mother has a history of a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=IM0YJg&anker=Za2185673cc278f4e363afb0a09c68c52\" data-learningcard-id=\"IM0YJg\" data-anker=\"Za2185673cc278f4e363afb0a09c68c52\" data-sememe-id=\"Go0BWS\">sexually transmitted infection</a>, did not receive <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=RN0lag&anker=Zf0d5d063dd37a8b7e921fe19446cd42e\" data-learningcard-id=\"RN0lag\" data-anker=\"Zf0d5d063dd37a8b7e921fe19446cd42e\">prenatal care</a>, and had a vaginal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3O0SHT&anker=Zb047f3b49dca9a23bb1a47397ef5964f\" data-learningcard-id=\"3O0SHT\" data-anker=\"Zb047f3b49dca9a23bb1a47397ef5964f\" data-section-id=\"GfbBnG\">birth</a>, all of which increase the risk of vertical <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zO0rET&anker=Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-learningcard-id=\"zO0rET\" data-anker=\"Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-section-id=\"CPbqSF\" data-sememe-id=\"4kY3L6\">HPV</a> transmission. <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Progressive</b></span> <span class=\"wichtig\"><b><span data-sememe-id=\"Z7dZ4r0\">hoarseness</span></b></span>, <span class=\"wichtig\"><b><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3L0Sxg&anker=Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\" data-learningcard-id=\"3L0Sxg\" data-anker=\"Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\">cough</a></b></span>, and <span class=\"wichtig\"><b><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Xq09CS&anker=Zec7af3634c75f9e5227d266d823e5ea7\" data-learningcard-id=\"Xq09CS\" data-anker=\"Zec7af3634c75f9e5227d266d823e5ea7\" data-sememe-id=\"KaYUln\">dyspnea</a></b></span> are typical of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-section-id=\"rtXfU-\" data-sememe-id=\"Btazfm\">RRP</a>. Other symptoms include <span class=\"wichtig\"><b><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Zc2f4107b6e40254227fa91ccae0a16aa\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Zc2f4107b6e40254227fa91ccae0a16aa\" data-section-id=\"LrXw3z\" data-sememe-id=\"JsXsDz\">dysphonia</a></b></span> or aphonia, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pu0Wr3&anker=Z69adc0ba2f6ffba815e3a63018221aa7\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pu0Wr3\" data-anker=\"Z69adc0ba2f6ffba815e3a63018221aa7\" data-section-id=\"xldE_J0\" data-sememe-id=\"7aY4Nn\">stridor</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=D501mg&anker=Zd2d195657240f493374e95e2b75cc8cf\" data-learningcard-id=\"D501mg\" data-anker=\"Zd2d195657240f493374e95e2b75cc8cf\" data-section-id=\"-ZXDV9\" data-sememe-id=\"IQ0Yxf\">dysphagia</a>. The diagnosis is typically established using <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=hl0c9T&anker=Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-learningcard-id=\"hl0c9T\" data-anker=\"Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-section-id=\"NCX-HZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"2ZbTaH\">laryngoscopy</a>, which shows <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>raspberry-like growths</b></span> located on the <span class=\"wichtig\"><b><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ajXQ_B\">vocal cords</a></b></span>. There is no definitive treatment for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-section-id=\"rtXfU-\" data-sememe-id=\"Btazfm\">RRP</a>. Management aims to limit the spread of disease via surgical excision of symptomatic lesions and potentially antiviral <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=TH06ph&anker=Zbe736188466767a56a07774a11dee306\" data-learningcard-id=\"TH06ph\" data-anker=\"Zbe736188466767a56a07774a11dee306\" data-section-id=\"l1WvS40\" data-sememe-id=\"3TYSqo\">adjuvant therapy</a> (e.g., <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=pm0Lgg&anker=Zd38b5038c3417dbbb9de1fa38742dc69\" data-learningcard-id=\"pm0Lgg\" data-anker=\"Zd38b5038c3417dbbb9de1fa38742dc69\" data-section-id=\"DBX1100\" data-sememe-id=\"GjXBby\">cidofovir</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4p03pS&anker=Z3b31a81be7b2d71eaed7bc41ce6e9b9b\" data-learningcard-id=\"4p03pS\" data-anker=\"Z3b31a81be7b2d71eaed7bc41ce6e9b9b\" data-section-id=\"D9c1pe0\" data-sememe-id=\"HgcK9b0\">interferon</a>). Complications include malignant transformation into <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z17c54b50884f6ae691e10c71ea7eccb6\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z17c54b50884f6ae691e10c71ea7eccb6\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\" data-sememe-id=\"prXLRz\">squamous cell carcinoma</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pu0Wr3&anker=Z3d448fb2ed2c100951ac1809901a7dc0\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pu0Wr3\" data-anker=\"Z3d448fb2ed2c100951ac1809901a7dc0\">airway obstruction</a>, and life-threatening <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tH0XHh&anker=Z33ef7cab5ec891b82794259be7e75d5d\" data-learningcard-id=\"tH0XHh\" data-anker=\"Z33ef7cab5ec891b82794259be7e75d5d\" data-section-id=\"Q-1uCj0\">respiratory distress</a>.<br><br>See “<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Zae0830f4d97b617d3d97b1029a9beb5c\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Zae0830f4d97b617d3d97b1029a9beb5c\" data-section-id=\"wBch1U0\">Differential diagnoses of benign laryngeal lesions</a>” table.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_5639fcbd723f9.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>Laryngoscopy of the vocal cords.</p><p>At the upper edge of the picture, at the front commissure, there are several pale pink &quot;raspberry shaped&quot; tumors on the mucous membrane. Below these there are other similar nodules.</p><p>This appearance is characteristic of laryngeal papilomatosis. </p></div></div></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Zf557981758a3b7ea77b722dd0dca95c7\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Zf557981758a3b7ea77b722dd0dca95c7\" data-section-id=\"qtXCe-\" data-sememe-id=\"hDYcVr\">Vocal fold nodules</a> are one of the most common causes of <span data-sememe-id=\"Z7dZ4r0\">hoarseness</span> in children and typically develop in boys. However, most <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Zf557981758a3b7ea77b722dd0dca95c7\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Zf557981758a3b7ea77b722dd0dca95c7\" data-section-id=\"qtXCe-\" data-sememe-id=\"hDYcVr\">vocal fold nodules</a> are seen in boys aged 5–10 years with a history of repeated trauma or <span data-sememe-id=\"nnW7FN0\">vocal abuse</span>. Moreover, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=hl0c9T&anker=Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-learningcard-id=\"hl0c9T\" data-anker=\"Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-section-id=\"NCX-HZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"2ZbTaH\">laryngoscopy</a> usually shows symmetrically distributed, pinhead-sized pale <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Ze562e7aa25e368f0be0c7066c00f0243\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Ze562e7aa25e368f0be0c7066c00f0243\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"YdXnoC\">nodules</a> on the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ajXQ_B\">vocal folds</a>, unlike the multiple polypoid asymmetrical growths seen in this patient.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_5081d933d9bbb.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>Laryngoscopic image of the vocal folds of an adult with increasing hoarseness of voice.</p><p>Right picture: vocal folds in the respiratory position. Pinhead sized tumors lie on both sides, between the middle and anterior thirds of the vocal folds (place of the highest oscillation amplitude).<br/>Left picture: same finding in phonation position.</p><p>Diagnosis: vocal cord nodules (phonation nodules).</p></div></div></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Z4578733ab8350320cc2ee34b62ab7f9f\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Z4578733ab8350320cc2ee34b62ab7f9f\" data-section-id=\"6tXje-\" data-sememe-id=\"9taNfm\">Reinke edema</a> can manifest with <span data-sememe-id=\"Z7dZ4r0\">hoarseness</span> and, in more severe cases, respiratory symptoms such as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3L0Sxg&anker=Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\" data-learningcard-id=\"3L0Sxg\" data-anker=\"Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\">cough</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Xq09CS&anker=Zec7af3634c75f9e5227d266d823e5ea7\" data-learningcard-id=\"Xq09CS\" data-anker=\"Zec7af3634c75f9e5227d266d823e5ea7\" data-sememe-id=\"KaYUln\">dyspnea</a>. However, this condition most commonly affects women aged 40–60 years with a history of smoking. In addition, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=hl0c9T&anker=Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-learningcard-id=\"hl0c9T\" data-anker=\"Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-section-id=\"NCX-HZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"2ZbTaH\">laryngoscopy</a> shows bilateral swelling of the true <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ajXQ_B\">vocal folds</a>, not asymmetric polypoid growths on both true and false <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ajXQ_B\">vocal folds</a>.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_62cad4313b0c90.98650140.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>Laryngoscopy</p><p>Loose, enlarged vocal cord due to a subepithelial edema between the epithelium and the vocal ligament (Reinke's space; green overlay).</p><p>Diagnosis: moderate Reinke's edema</p></div></div></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<span data-sememe-id=\"fMWkLN0\">Vocal fold retention cysts</span> may manifest with <span data-sememe-id=\"Z7dZ4r0\">hoarseness</span> and possible <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Xq09CS&anker=Zec7af3634c75f9e5227d266d823e5ea7\" data-learningcard-id=\"Xq09CS\" data-anker=\"Zec7af3634c75f9e5227d266d823e5ea7\" data-sememe-id=\"KaYUln\">dyspnea</a>. However, most <span data-sememe-id=\"fMWkLN0\">vocal fold retention cysts</span> develop in adults with a history of vocal stress (e.g., professional singers). Children may develop <span data-sememe-id=\"gMWFLN0\">epidermoid vocal fold cysts</span> as a result of a congenital anomaly of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ajXQ_B\">vocal cords</a>. Both retention and <span data-sememe-id=\"gMWFLN0\">epidermoid vocal fold cysts</span> are, however, characterized by a well-defined unilateral yellow-white lesion of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ajXQ_B\">vocal cords</a> on <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=hl0c9T&anker=Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-learningcard-id=\"hl0c9T\" data-anker=\"Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-section-id=\"NCX-HZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"2ZbTaH\">laryngoscopy</a> rather than polypoid asymmetrical growths like the ones seen here.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_65980d1b930994.82664593.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=yj0d1T&anker=Zb4a31eef2a931ffa97b90ecbd5ef334c\" data-learningcard-id=\"yj0d1T\" data-anker=\"Zb4a31eef2a931ffa97b90ecbd5ef334c\" data-sememe-id=\"IZbY1H\">Chronic laryngitis</a> can manifest with <span data-sememe-id=\"Z7dZ4r0\">hoarseness</span> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3L0Sxg&anker=Z015b818530f4e9e6346353e66813fabc\" data-learningcard-id=\"3L0Sxg\" data-anker=\"Z015b818530f4e9e6346353e66813fabc\" data-section-id=\"5y1ifj0\" data-sememe-id=\"PVdWuK0\">chronic cough</a>. However, the diagnosis of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=yj0d1T&anker=Zb4a31eef2a931ffa97b90ecbd5ef334c\" data-learningcard-id=\"yj0d1T\" data-anker=\"Zb4a31eef2a931ffa97b90ecbd5ef334c\" data-sememe-id=\"IZbY1H\">chronic laryngitis</a> is usually established if symptoms persist for more than three weeks whereas this patient has had symptoms for only two weeks. In addition, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=hl0c9T&anker=Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-learningcard-id=\"hl0c9T\" data-anker=\"Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-section-id=\"NCX-HZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"2ZbTaH\">laryngoscopy</a> usually shows mucus, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z2402afe504766ef84f64acad4aaea47b\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z2402afe504766ef84f64acad4aaea47b\" data-section-id=\"0vXeA-\" data-sememe-id=\"3wYSir\">erythema</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=SM0yLg&anker=Zc00dca4994157e86d8e6e8ee9510443f\" data-learningcard-id=\"SM0yLg\" data-anker=\"Zc00dca4994157e86d8e6e8ee9510443f\" data-section-id=\"JcXsWC\" data-sememe-id=\"Oo0IXS\">edema</a> of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Z917870fa18c05b025cc3696075936299\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Z917870fa18c05b025cc3696075936299\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">posterior</a> laryngeal wall with possible <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=VP0GdT&anker=Za78e93e8d8af6655bfa6f64569ad19e2\" data-learningcard-id=\"VP0GdT\" data-anker=\"Za78e93e8d8af6655bfa6f64569ad19e2\" data-section-id=\"aFXQg-\" data-sememe-id=\"dwYo3r\">atrophy</a> rather than polypoid growths of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ajXQ_B\">vocal folds</a>.</div>",
      "hint": "The absence of prenatal care increases the risk of developing this condition.",
