    {
      "text": "A 5-year-old girl who was born full term presents for evaluation of hoarseness that has worsened during the past 2 years. Her father describes her voice as “raspy” and notes that it worsens throughout the day. Sometimes, the girl is unable to speak clearly or loses her voice by the end of the day. Her father notes that she has become shy and often avoids playing with her peers at preschool. She is the youngest of five siblings, and her father reports that they have a loud household.\nShe has not had any shortness of breath, stridor, throat clearing, or symptoms of dysphagia or heartburn. She has a history of allergic rhinitis for which she has been taking cetirizine daily. She has never been intubated and has not had any surgical procedures.\nShe is afebrile with a respiratory rate of 18 breaths per minute, and her physical examination is normal.\nWhat is the most likely cause of this patient’s hoarseness?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "An adverse effect of cetirizine"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Laryngeal foreign body"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Vocal cord nodules"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Vocal cord paralysis"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Laryngopharyngeal reflux"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pm0Wfg&anker=Z061bef81bf51e9b42ad18eb6b8d2a773\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pm0Wfg\" data-anker=\"Z061bef81bf51e9b42ad18eb6b8d2a773\" data-sememe-id=\"A4aRNk\">antihistamine</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pm0Wfg&anker=Zebef3b35332bb43e10db5bed001cbb76\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pm0Wfg\" data-anker=\"Zebef3b35332bb43e10db5bed001cbb76\" data-section-id=\"cScaAb0\" data-sememe-id=\"z4arNk\">cetirizine</a> has known <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sN0tcg&anker=Zb7481497ac4d62e47bd9fb8e6aa6b45a\" data-learningcard-id=\"sN0tcg\" data-anker=\"Zb7481497ac4d62e47bd9fb8e6aa6b45a\" data-section-id=\"mIbVWE\">anticholinergic effects</a> that can result in decreased mucus production and <span data-sememe-id=\"Z7dZ4r0\">hoarseness</span>. Although stopping this medication in this patient might be helpful, a different condition is the more likely cause of her <span data-sememe-id=\"Z7dZ4r0\">hoarseness</span> and should be evaluated accordingly.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>Although a laryngeal foreign body might lead to <span data-sememe-id=\"Z7dZ4r0\">hoarseness</span> in addition to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pu0Wr3&anker=Z69adc0ba2f6ffba815e3a63018221aa7\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pu0Wr3\" data-anker=\"Z69adc0ba2f6ffba815e3a63018221aa7\" data-section-id=\"xldE_J0\" data-sememe-id=\"7aY4Nn\">stridor</a>, the time course of this patient’s symptoms (&gt; 2 years) makes this an unlikely diagnosis.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) CORRECT:</h4>The differential diagnosis for pediatric <span data-sememe-id=\"Z7dZ4r0\">hoarseness</span> can be broad. Diagnoses to consider include <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ajXQ_B\">vocal cord</a> pathology (e.g., <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Z6251da6a569c47455f57936d87b95bf8\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Z6251da6a569c47455f57936d87b95bf8\" data-section-id=\"LrXw3z\" data-sememe-id=\"-EWDyM0\">vocal cord paralysis</a>), <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ajXQ_B\">vocal cord</a> lesions (e.g., <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Ze562e7aa25e368f0be0c7066c00f0243\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Ze562e7aa25e368f0be0c7066c00f0243\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"YdXnoC\">nodules</a>, cysts, polyps), <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z98519ebae0e17b261f3ee4e6d5779a48\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z98519ebae0e17b261f3ee4e6d5779a48\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\">benign tumors</a> (e.g., <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-section-id=\"rtXfU-\" data-sememe-id=\"Btazfm\">laryngeal papillomatosis</a>), congenital lesions (e.g., laryngeal webs), <span data-sememe-id=\"Ysdntr0\">laryngopharyngeal reflux</span>, and functional (nonanatomic) disorders. Most cases of pediatric <span data-sememe-id=\"Z7dZ4r0\">hoarseness</span> are related to benign lesions or functional disorders. A thorough history that elicits chronicity, impact, and any associated <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ap0QLS&anker=Z5a964768554f93e7967999032fda236f\" data-learningcard-id=\"ap0QLS\" data-anker=\"Z5a964768554f93e7967999032fda236f\">airway</a> symptoms, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=D501mg&anker=Zd2d195657240f493374e95e2b75cc8cf\" data-learningcard-id=\"D501mg\" data-anker=\"Zd2d195657240f493374e95e2b75cc8cf\" data-section-id=\"-ZXDV9\" data-sememe-id=\"IQ0Yxf\">dysphagia</a>, or reflux symptoms is critical for narrowing the diagnosis and assessing the timing of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=hl0c9T&anker=Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-learningcard-id=\"hl0c9T\" data-anker=\"Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-section-id=\"NCX-HZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"2ZbTaH\">laryngoscopy</a>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=hl0c9T&anker=Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-learningcard-id=\"hl0c9T\" data-anker=\"Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-section-id=\"NCX-HZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"2ZbTaH\">Laryngoscopy</a> enables visualization of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Zdc6918bc99931ac9e8b52ff7eb53beda\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Zdc6918bc99931ac9e8b52ff7eb53beda\">larynx</a> and is imperative to rule out more sinister causes of <span data-sememe-id=\"Z7dZ4r0\">hoarseness</span> (e.g., <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-section-id=\"rtXfU-\" data-sememe-id=\"Btazfm\">laryngeal papillomatosis</a>), allowing for initiation of appropriate treatment. This patient’s presentation — chronic misuse or overuse of the voice with symptoms of worsening <span data-sememe-id=\"Z7dZ4r0\">hoarseness</span> throughout the day and voice loss — is classic for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Zf557981758a3b7ea77b722dd0dca95c7\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Zf557981758a3b7ea77b722dd0dca95c7\" data-section-id=\"qtXCe-\" data-sememe-id=\"hDYcVr\">vocal cord nodules</a>. These lesions are the most common cause of pediatric voice disorders associated with voice overuse or misuse, particularly in the preschool age group. The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Ze562e7aa25e368f0be0c7066c00f0243\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Ze562e7aa25e368f0be0c7066c00f0243\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"YdXnoC\">nodules</a> result from mechanical trauma that incites inflammation, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=SM0yLg&anker=Zc00dca4994157e86d8e6e8ee9510443f\" data-learningcard-id=\"SM0yLg\" data-anker=\"Zc00dca4994157e86d8e6e8ee9510443f\" data-section-id=\"JcXsWC\" data-sememe-id=\"Oo0IXS\">edema</a>, and eventually <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ro0fWS&anker=Zf29b9e7e01bf75d0402e969b50992d30\" data-learningcard-id=\"ro0fWS\" data-anker=\"Zf29b9e7e01bf75d0402e969b50992d30\" data-section-id=\"H9cKKe0\" data-sememe-id=\"yi0d8f\">fibrosis</a> at the free edge of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ajXQ_B\">vocal cord</a>, ultimately hampering voice production. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Zf557981758a3b7ea77b722dd0dca95c7\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Zf557981758a3b7ea77b722dd0dca95c7\" data-section-id=\"qtXCe-\" data-sememe-id=\"hDYcVr\">Vocal cord nodules</a> can be diagnosed via <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=hl0c9T&anker=Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-learningcard-id=\"hl0c9T\" data-anker=\"Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-section-id=\"NCX-HZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"2ZbTaH\">laryngoscopy</a>.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point:</b></span> Prolonged <span data-sememe-id=\"Z7dZ4r0\">hoarseness</span> in a <span data-sememe-id=\"QQWuDO0\">preschool-age child</span> with voice overuse and no <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ap0QLS&anker=Z5a964768554f93e7967999032fda236f\" data-learningcard-id=\"ap0QLS\" data-anker=\"Z5a964768554f93e7967999032fda236f\">airway</a> symptoms, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=D501mg&anker=Zd2d195657240f493374e95e2b75cc8cf\" data-learningcard-id=\"D501mg\" data-anker=\"Zd2d195657240f493374e95e2b75cc8cf\" data-section-id=\"-ZXDV9\" data-sememe-id=\"IQ0Yxf\">dysphagia</a>, or reflux symptoms is likely due to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Zf557981758a3b7ea77b722dd0dca95c7\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Zf557981758a3b7ea77b722dd0dca95c7\" data-section-id=\"qtXCe-\" data-sememe-id=\"hDYcVr\">vocal cord nodules</a> that can be diagnosed with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=hl0c9T&anker=Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-learningcard-id=\"hl0c9T\" data-anker=\"Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-section-id=\"NCX-HZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"2ZbTaH\">laryngoscopy</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Z6251da6a569c47455f57936d87b95bf8\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Z6251da6a569c47455f57936d87b95bf8\" data-section-id=\"LrXw3z\" data-sememe-id=\"-EWDyM0\">Vocal cord paralysis</a> is a common cause of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Zc2f4107b6e40254227fa91ccae0a16aa\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Zc2f4107b6e40254227fa91ccae0a16aa\" data-section-id=\"LrXw3z\" data-sememe-id=\"JsXsDz\">dysphonia</a> in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a40Q3T&anker=Z0fc257b9a869b8bf01b45c4fb73dbdc1\" data-learningcard-id=\"a40Q3T\" data-anker=\"Z0fc257b9a869b8bf01b45c4fb73dbdc1\" data-section-id=\"_8X56-\" data-sememe-id=\"4Qb3wt\">infants</a> and is typically <span data-sememe-id=\"Qh0udf\">iatrogenic</span>. Causes include cardiac <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7I04Vh&anker=Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-learningcard-id=\"7I04Vh\" data-anker=\"Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-section-id=\"w41hlS0\">surgery</a> (e.g., <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4403jT&anker=Z8f082bb5e397f97b9f62337c71bebf15\" data-learningcard-id=\"4403jT\" data-anker=\"Z8f082bb5e397f97b9f62337c71bebf15\" data-section-id=\"SEXyE-\" data-sememe-id=\"VCaGI5\">patent ductus arteriosus</a> ligation), <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wl0h_T&anker=Z21eeb82b6c053cc0ed27a0cb781354fa\" data-learningcard-id=\"wl0h_T\" data-anker=\"Z21eeb82b6c053cc0ed27a0cb781354fa\">thyroid surgery</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=hl0c9T&anker=Z35189a36e3ecbd4acce6b05b19ab088d\" data-learningcard-id=\"hl0c9T\" data-anker=\"Z35189a36e3ecbd4acce6b05b19ab088d\" data-section-id=\"kCXmHZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"70Y4hn\">intubation</a>. This patient does not have a history of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7I04Vh&anker=Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-learningcard-id=\"7I04Vh\" data-anker=\"Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-section-id=\"w41hlS0\">surgery</a> or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=hl0c9T&anker=Z35189a36e3ecbd4acce6b05b19ab088d\" data-learningcard-id=\"hl0c9T\" data-anker=\"Z35189a36e3ecbd4acce6b05b19ab088d\" data-section-id=\"kCXmHZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"70Y4hn\">intubation</a>; thus, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Z6251da6a569c47455f57936d87b95bf8\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Z6251da6a569c47455f57936d87b95bf8\" data-section-id=\"LrXw3z\" data-sememe-id=\"-EWDyM0\">vocal cord paralysis</a> is less likely.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<span data-sememe-id=\"Ysdntr0\">Laryngopharyngeal reflux</span> can contribute to <span data-sememe-id=\"Z7dZ4r0\">hoarseness</span>; however, this patient is not exhibiting any other symptoms of gastroesophageal or <span data-sememe-id=\"Ysdntr0\">laryngopharyngeal reflux</span>, such as throat clearing or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=vg0AC2&anker=Zb8f67c61f09e7d417c5481e544947a84\" data-learningcard-id=\"vg0AC2\" data-anker=\"Zb8f67c61f09e7d417c5481e544947a84\" data-section-id=\"580iM3\" data-sememe-id=\"ML1Myh0\">heartburn</a>. Empiric antireflux therapy should be avoided until other laryngeal lesions have been ruled out with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=hl0c9T&anker=Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-learningcard-id=\"hl0c9T\" data-anker=\"Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-section-id=\"NCX-HZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"2ZbTaH\">laryngoscopy</a>.</div>",
