    {
      "text": "A 3-year-old boy is brought in by his parents for evaluation of hoarseness. They state that he has been hoarse for as long as they can remember, at least 2 years, and that he has never had any illnesses or taken any medications. They are not aware of any underlying medical conditions. During the past several days, they have noted shortness of breath and noisier breathing on inspiration.\nOn examination, the patient is hoarse and has audible biphasic stridor. There is a mild degree of neck retraction but no signs of respiratory distress, and the child is otherwise comfortable. He has an oxygen saturation of 100% while breathing ambient air and is afebrile, with no evidence of rhinorrhea or cough. His lung fields are clear bilaterally. He has no lesions along the face or chin.\nAirway radiographs reveal no narrowing of the subglottic region.\nWhich one of the following diagnoses is most likely in this case?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Recurrent respiratory papillomatosis"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Fungal laryngitis"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Laryngopharyngeal reflux"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Subglottic hemangioma"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Bilateral vocal cord nodules"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) CORRECT:</h4>Respiratory papillomatosis is the most likely cause of this patient’s chronic <span data-sememe-id=\"Z7dZ4r0\">hoarseness</span> and acute <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pu0Wr3&anker=Z69adc0ba2f6ffba815e3a63018221aa7\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pu0Wr3\" data-anker=\"Z69adc0ba2f6ffba815e3a63018221aa7\" data-section-id=\"xldE_J0\" data-sememe-id=\"7aY4Nn\">stridor</a>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-section-id=\"rtXfU-\" data-sememe-id=\"Btazfm\">Recurrent respiratory papillomatosis</a> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-section-id=\"rtXfU-\" data-sememe-id=\"Btazfm\">RRP</a>) is caused by infection with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zO0rET&anker=Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-learningcard-id=\"zO0rET\" data-anker=\"Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-section-id=\"CPbqSF\" data-sememe-id=\"4kY3L6\">human papillomavirus</a>, thought to be acquired in utero, and classically manifests with long-standing <span data-sememe-id=\"Z7dZ4r0\">hoarseness</span> secondary to the location of the disease on the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ajXQ_B\">vocal cords</a>. Unrecognized growth of the papillomas can lead to an obstructive phenomenon and to biphasic <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pu0Wr3&anker=Z69adc0ba2f6ffba815e3a63018221aa7\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pu0Wr3\" data-anker=\"Z69adc0ba2f6ffba815e3a63018221aa7\" data-section-id=\"xldE_J0\" data-sememe-id=\"7aY4Nn\">stridor</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tH0XHh&anker=Z33ef7cab5ec891b82794259be7e75d5d\" data-learningcard-id=\"tH0XHh\" data-anker=\"Z33ef7cab5ec891b82794259be7e75d5d\" data-section-id=\"Q-1uCj0\">respiratory distress</a>.<br><br>Definitive diagnosis of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-section-id=\"rtXfU-\" data-sememe-id=\"Btazfm\">RRP</a> can be made with <span data-sememe-id=\"94bNlF\">flexible laryngoscopy</span>.<br><br>Treatment typically consists of surgical <span data-sememe-id=\"2QcTvX0\">debulking</span> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=TH06ph&anker=Zbe736188466767a56a07774a11dee306\" data-learningcard-id=\"TH06ph\" data-anker=\"Zbe736188466767a56a07774a11dee306\" data-section-id=\"l1WvS40\" data-sememe-id=\"3TYSqo\">adjuvant therapy</a>, for which there are many options. Patients often need multiple procedures at intervals determined by their symptoms.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point:</b></span> Chronic worsening <span data-sememe-id=\"Z7dZ4r0\">hoarseness</span> leading to acute <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pu0Wr3&anker=Z69adc0ba2f6ffba815e3a63018221aa7\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pu0Wr3\" data-anker=\"Z69adc0ba2f6ffba815e3a63018221aa7\" data-section-id=\"xldE_J0\" data-sememe-id=\"7aY4Nn\">stridor</a> in a child is most consistent with respiratory papillomatosis.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_65e5d6d5db4080.69001263.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>Laryngoscopy of the vocal cords.<br/><br/>Widespread papillomatous lesions are visible along the false and true vocal folds, leading to airway obstruction.</p></div></div></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>Fungal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=yj0d1T&anker=Zb4a31eef2a931ffa97b90ecbd5ef334c\" data-learningcard-id=\"yj0d1T\" data-anker=\"Zb4a31eef2a931ffa97b90ecbd5ef334c\" data-sememe-id=\"IZbY1H\">laryngitis</a> and <span data-sememe-id=\"Ysdntr0\">laryngopharyngeal reflux</span> can manifest with some of the same symptoms as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-section-id=\"rtXfU-\" data-sememe-id=\"Btazfm\">RRP</a>. However, fungal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=yj0d1T&anker=Zb4a31eef2a931ffa97b90ecbd5ef334c\" data-learningcard-id=\"yj0d1T\" data-anker=\"Zb4a31eef2a931ffa97b90ecbd5ef334c\" data-sememe-id=\"IZbY1H\">laryngitis</a> is associated with a history of inhaler use and will not cause chronic voice changes.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<span data-sememe-id=\"Ysdntr0\">Laryngopharyngeal reflux</span> may result in fluctuating <span data-sememe-id=\"Z7dZ4r0\">hoarseness</span> but does not lead to acute <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pu0Wr3&anker=Z3d448fb2ed2c100951ac1809901a7dc0\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pu0Wr3\" data-anker=\"Z3d448fb2ed2c100951ac1809901a7dc0\">airway obstruction</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pu0Wr3&anker=Z69adc0ba2f6ffba815e3a63018221aa7\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pu0Wr3\" data-anker=\"Z69adc0ba2f6ffba815e3a63018221aa7\" data-section-id=\"xldE_J0\" data-sememe-id=\"7aY4Nn\">stridor</a> in children.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>A <span data-sememe-id=\"gVdFFK0\">subglottic hemangioma</span> is less likely than <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-section-id=\"rtXfU-\" data-sememe-id=\"Btazfm\">RRP</a> in this patient, given that the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ap0QLS&anker=Z5a964768554f93e7967999032fda236f\" data-learningcard-id=\"ap0QLS\" data-anker=\"Z5a964768554f93e7967999032fda236f\">airway</a> radiographs were negative for any <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z05fee0699df76e03ef761015d2bf694b\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z05fee0699df76e03ef761015d2bf694b\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"K0cUSa0\">subglottic</a> pathology and <span data-sememe-id=\"gVdFFK0\">subglottic hemangiomas</span> tend to manifest with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pu0Wr3&anker=Z69adc0ba2f6ffba815e3a63018221aa7\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pu0Wr3\" data-anker=\"Z69adc0ba2f6ffba815e3a63018221aa7\" data-section-id=\"xldE_J0\" data-sememe-id=\"7aY4Nn\">stridor</a> in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a40Q3T&anker=Z0fc257b9a869b8bf01b45c4fb73dbdc1\" data-learningcard-id=\"a40Q3T\" data-anker=\"Z0fc257b9a869b8bf01b45c4fb73dbdc1\" data-section-id=\"_8X56-\" data-sememe-id=\"4Qb3wt\">infancy</a>, not <span data-sememe-id=\"Z7dZ4r0\">hoarseness</span>. Imaging in a patient with <span data-sememe-id=\"gVdFFK0\">subglottic hemangioma</span> would be expected to show an asymmetric fullness in the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z05fee0699df76e03ef761015d2bf694b\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z05fee0699df76e03ef761015d2bf694b\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"K0cUSa0\">subglottis</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>Early <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Za3de18b26b32ec1f4ede0e0abbcc6d10\" data-section-id=\"rtXfU-\" data-sememe-id=\"Btazfm\">RRP</a> can often be misinterpreted as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Zf557981758a3b7ea77b722dd0dca95c7\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Zf557981758a3b7ea77b722dd0dca95c7\" data-section-id=\"qtXCe-\" data-sememe-id=\"hDYcVr\">vocal cord nodules</a>, but such <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Ze562e7aa25e368f0be0c7066c00f0243\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Ze562e7aa25e368f0be0c7066c00f0243\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"YdXnoC\">nodules</a> are associated with voice changes only, not <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pu0Wr3&anker=Z6471ed418d8d3123f9404a9f9278ac23\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pu0Wr3\" data-anker=\"Z6471ed418d8d3123f9404a9f9278ac23\" data-section-id=\"xldE_J0\" data-sememe-id=\"KOVUtu0\">inspiratory stridor</a>, and they rarely, if ever, lead to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pu0Wr3&anker=Z3d448fb2ed2c100951ac1809901a7dc0\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pu0Wr3\" data-anker=\"Z3d448fb2ed2c100951ac1809901a7dc0\">airway obstruction</a> or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tH0XHh&anker=Z33ef7cab5ec891b82794259be7e75d5d\" data-learningcard-id=\"tH0XHh\" data-anker=\"Z33ef7cab5ec891b82794259be7e75d5d\" data-section-id=\"Q-1uCj0\">respiratory distress</a>. When viewed on <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=hl0c9T&anker=Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-learningcard-id=\"hl0c9T\" data-anker=\"Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-section-id=\"NCX-HZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"2ZbTaH\">laryngoscopy</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zj0r1T&anker=Zf557981758a3b7ea77b722dd0dca95c7\" data-learningcard-id=\"zj0r1T\" data-anker=\"Zf557981758a3b7ea77b722dd0dca95c7\" data-section-id=\"qtXCe-\" data-sememe-id=\"hDYcVr\">vocal cord nodules</a> are pale in color and found in the mid- or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Z611d380c96ce797875c8e46c949415ed\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Z611d380c96ce797875c8e46c949415ed\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">anterior</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ajXQ_B\">vocal cord</a>, secondary to their formation from <span data-sememe-id=\"nnW7FN0\">vocal abuse</span>.</div>",
